WEBVTT

00:00.327 --> 00:02.327
<i>Previously on Another Period</i>

00:02.602 --> 00:04.101
<i>I'm leaving Bellacourt.</i>

00:04.170 --> 00:06.070
You are the head butler now.

00:06.138 --> 00:07.872
We are brother and sister!

00:07.939 --> 00:09.840
- It's over, Frederick.
- No.

00:09.909 --> 00:12.977
You're a useless, unlovable,
vile, tacky little thing.

00:13.045 --> 00:15.346
- [SCREAMING]
- [BODY THUDS]

00:15.414 --> 00:16.814
[CRYING]

00:16.883 --> 00:18.315
[SPRIGHTLY MUSIC]

00:18.384 --> 00:19.411
What is it?

00:20.119 --> 00:22.033
It's... a cone

00:22.361 --> 00:24.245
of iced cream!

00:24.385 --> 00:26.089
It's just in from Paris.

00:26.365 --> 00:29.566
Oh, I get it. Your tongue is the spoon.

00:30.353 --> 00:31.435
[CRUNCHING]

00:33.539 --> 00:34.670
Thank you.

00:35.341 --> 00:37.240
They've arrived! They've arrived!

00:37.309 --> 00:39.643
The invitation to Celery Savoy Bellacourt's

00:39.712 --> 00:41.578
masquerade ball have arrived.

00:41.647 --> 00:43.046
Ooh! Maybe I'll wear

00:43.115 --> 00:44.915
Cleopatra's menstrual napkins as a mask.

00:44.984 --> 00:46.283
New and used.

00:46.352 --> 00:48.185
I wanna wear Blanche's skin as a mask.

00:48.253 --> 00:50.153
Peepers, will you get my face scissors?

00:50.222 --> 00:51.989
My face is not removable.

00:52.057 --> 00:54.057
Yes, uh, Miss Beatrice, might I remind you

00:54.126 --> 00:56.593
I am Garfield, and I
am the head butler now?

00:56.662 --> 00:58.462
We call all our butlers Peepers.

00:58.530 --> 01:01.431
Yes. It's easier than
remembering a new name.

01:01.456 --> 01:02.517
Yes, of course.

01:02.542 --> 01:04.066
We're opening our own envelopes now?

01:04.135 --> 01:05.609
What are we, co-miners?

01:06.538 --> 01:09.228
I can't wait to seduce Colonel
Beauregard Trimbald at the ball.

01:09.253 --> 01:11.587
"Kernel"? Is he a man or is he a corn?

01:11.655 --> 01:14.571
He's the Toilet King of
Tallahassee, and he's available.

01:15.459 --> 01:17.245
How do you even eat this?

01:17.245 --> 01:18.244
[HUFFS]

01:20.247 --> 01:22.615
"Cordially not invited"?

01:23.097 --> 01:24.760
Why wouldn't Celery invite us?

01:24.966 --> 01:27.889
Don't tell me she's still
mad because I impaled her sister

01:27.889 --> 01:29.302
crotch-first at last year's

01:29.370 --> 01:30.640
Winter Wonderland Reindeer Roasting Ball.

01:31.408 --> 01:33.275
- People change!
- It's true.

01:33.343 --> 01:34.843
I once saw a person change from being

01:34.912 --> 01:36.745
"not on fire" to "on fire."

01:37.251 --> 01:38.346
It was because of me.

01:38.415 --> 01:40.997
Um, if you're not going to
the ball, could we stop now?

01:41.285 --> 01:43.351
We are going to that ball.

01:44.388 --> 01:45.935
[CRUNCH]

01:46.290 --> 01:48.723
Blanche, you got ice cream on my mask!

01:50.027 --> 01:52.394
<i>♪ I want the money, I want the fame ♪</i>

01:52.462 --> 01:54.763
<i>♪ I want the whole world to know my name ♪</i>

01:54.831 --> 01:57.132
<i>♪ This is mine, I got to get it ♪</i>

01:57.200 --> 01:59.601
<i>♪ I got to get it, got, got to get it ♪</i>

01:59.670 --> 02:01.069
<i>♪ "Another Period" ♪</i>

02:02.147 --> 02:04.387
Synced and corrected by louvette
www.addic7ed.com

02:04.641 --> 02:06.107
In a surprising turn of events,

02:06.176 --> 02:08.476
<i>turns out life outside Bellacourt Manor</i>

02:08.544 --> 02:09.978
<i>can be deeply relaxing.</i>

02:10.047 --> 02:11.146
No, Shenandoah,

02:11.214 --> 02:13.315
the proper technique for making acorn mush

02:13.383 --> 02:15.650
is with a loose wrist.

02:15.719 --> 02:19.321
Let your wrist flow like a bounding elk.

02:19.841 --> 02:22.257
Hmm? Oh! [CHUCKLES] Me?

02:22.326 --> 02:23.592
No, yes, I've been

02:23.660 --> 02:25.927
the head butler for two weeks now, and...

02:25.996 --> 02:29.531
[CHUCKLES] It's been quite... relaxing.

02:29.600 --> 02:30.832
- Garfield!
- Yes?

02:30.901 --> 02:32.133
We have an emergency!

02:32.202 --> 02:33.835
We ran out of cacao for the ganache,

02:33.904 --> 02:36.638
and Miss Beatrice is holding
her breath until we get more.

02:36.707 --> 02:38.273
Where is the swan fat?

02:38.342 --> 02:40.375
Oh, you know Lady Dodo will only eat birds

02:40.444 --> 02:42.143
if they're fried in the fat of other birds.

02:42.212 --> 02:44.813
Garfield! Where's the goddamn lamé

02:44.881 --> 02:46.982
for Frederick's golden shoulder pads?

02:47.050 --> 02:49.985
A week ago, I requested
French rolling pins.

02:50.053 --> 02:52.621
French! These break off
in a sphincter immediately!

02:52.689 --> 02:54.189
- Don't smell that!
- We need answers.

02:54.257 --> 02:55.388
Garfield!

02:55.726 --> 02:57.125
Weren't you just saying that there's cacao

02:57.194 --> 02:59.194
hidden behind the turnips
in the root cellar?

02:59.262 --> 03:01.896
Yes! Uh, that's what I always say!

03:01.965 --> 03:03.264
And weren't you also saying

03:03.333 --> 03:05.066
to give Lady Dodo an absinthe lollipop

03:05.135 --> 03:06.901
until we can slaughter
and render the swans?

03:06.970 --> 03:08.370
And the lamé is in the lamé closet,

03:08.438 --> 03:09.804
between the silver and the ivory.

03:09.873 --> 03:13.141
Uh, I... don't really
give a shit about that.

03:13.210 --> 03:15.043
And Dr. Goldberg mustn't be allowed

03:15.112 --> 03:17.216
access to any long tools.

03:17.614 --> 03:20.548
Yes, that's... right!
That's what I was saying.

03:20.617 --> 03:22.050
Back to work, everyone!

03:22.119 --> 03:24.084
Oh, Flobelle, Flobelle. Um...

03:24.521 --> 03:27.022
I just wanted to thank you
for helping me slightly,

03:27.090 --> 03:28.890
in a very small way.

03:28.959 --> 03:30.825
We make a good team, Garfield.

03:30.894 --> 03:33.196
Yes. Team Garfield.

03:33.863 --> 03:36.998
Well, back to work! Scoot along, let's go!

03:37.067 --> 03:38.633
That's a good girl.

03:38.702 --> 03:42.270
[ELECTRONIC WALTZ MUSIC]

03:42.339 --> 03:49.344
♪

03:50.914 --> 03:53.014
Can you please stop what you're doing

03:53.083 --> 03:55.316
so we can discuss your
mission for the night?

03:55.385 --> 03:56.818
To be the queen of the dance floor!

03:56.887 --> 03:59.187
No, to form a political alliance

03:59.256 --> 04:00.488
with Colonel Trimbald.

04:00.557 --> 04:01.890
He's the most powerful member

04:01.958 --> 04:04.025
of the National Restroom Association.

04:04.094 --> 04:06.194
The N.R.A. You know, "Big Toilet."

04:06.475 --> 04:07.629
Stop dancing.

04:08.072 --> 04:09.365
I need you to stop.

04:09.433 --> 04:10.398
You're still dancing.

04:10.467 --> 04:11.721
I am not dancing. I stopped.

04:12.327 --> 04:14.402
I mean, you're moving.
Your... your head is moving.

04:14.471 --> 04:16.237
I'm listening, that's how I... fine.

04:16.305 --> 04:17.872
- Just... thank you.
- Fine.

04:17.940 --> 04:18.916
Thank you.

04:19.640 --> 04:21.046
If you can win his...

04:23.461 --> 04:25.067
I was trying to put my hat on.

04:25.757 --> 04:27.082
If we can win his support,

04:27.150 --> 04:29.617
our coffers will be positively overflowing

04:29.686 --> 04:32.287
with toilet money for
your presidential campaign.

04:33.208 --> 04:35.190
I'm running for president?

04:35.258 --> 04:36.524
[SWELLING WALTZ MUSIC]

04:36.593 --> 04:38.359
Oh, fantastic!

04:38.428 --> 04:44.866
♪

04:46.203 --> 04:48.403
<i>Sorry, Celery, but it's going to take</i>

04:48.472 --> 04:50.171
more than clear, explicit instructions

04:50.240 --> 04:53.508
to stay away from a party
to keep me from a party.

04:54.233 --> 04:56.010
There's nothing I hate
more than the hierarchy

04:56.079 --> 04:57.312
between the have-everythings

04:57.380 --> 04:59.314
and the have-everythings
but-an-invitation.

04:59.675 --> 05:01.015
It does look like a nice party, though.

05:01.084 --> 05:03.084
Now I see why we weren't invited.

05:03.416 --> 05:04.953
We have to get in there!

05:05.021 --> 05:06.421
Why don't we go through
the servants' entrance?

05:06.490 --> 05:08.690
- That seems easy.
- Might also be easy

05:08.759 --> 05:10.725
for me to cut my body into a hundred pieces

05:10.794 --> 05:12.594
and ship it to the party
via the Pony Express

05:12.662 --> 05:14.462
but I'm not going to do
that, because, much like

05:14.531 --> 05:17.306
entering the servants'
entrance, that would kill me!

05:17.996 --> 05:19.134
I'll meet you inside.

05:21.440 --> 05:23.905
Servants' entrance. Ah!

05:30.814 --> 05:33.782
[LIBRETTO FROM "THE MARRIAGE OF FIGARO"]

05:33.850 --> 05:40.855
♪

05:45.262 --> 05:46.928
Yes, yes!

05:46.997 --> 05:49.764
Wonderful humor, wonderful! [CHUCKLES]

05:50.567 --> 05:52.000
Colonel Trimbald!

05:52.068 --> 05:53.735
I'm so delighted you could make it.

05:53.804 --> 05:56.337
Oh, is that Endive Savoy-Sweetzer?

05:56.406 --> 05:58.039
You know my sister, Celery.

05:58.108 --> 06:00.008
- Charmed.
- Yes.

06:00.076 --> 06:01.476
How's business, Colonel?

06:01.545 --> 06:03.711
Well, I have to tip my
cap to the Supreme Court

06:03.780 --> 06:05.780
for upholding segregation.

06:05.849 --> 06:07.248
It's been great for business.

06:07.317 --> 06:08.583
It's double the toilets,

06:08.652 --> 06:10.385
and the black ones don't even need to work!

06:10.453 --> 06:12.353
- [LAUGHTER]
- Oh, that is fascinating.

06:12.422 --> 06:13.988
My husband, the vice president,

06:14.057 --> 06:16.090
has always been a huge
supporter of Big Toilet.

06:16.159 --> 06:17.425
You'll have to meet him.

06:17.728 --> 06:19.295
Where is Freddy?

06:24.406 --> 06:25.400
[QUIETLY] Ooh!

06:25.468 --> 06:28.903
Ah! I was going to eat that, madam!

06:29.992 --> 06:31.040
So was I.

06:31.504 --> 06:33.004
I love panda balls.

06:34.544 --> 06:35.860
Especially in the bathtub.

06:36.646 --> 06:38.055
- Really?
- Mm.

06:38.315 --> 06:41.082
It's rare to meet someone who
also enjoys meals in water.

06:41.151 --> 06:43.518
Do you also take your "hors deh-oovers"

06:43.587 --> 06:44.652
while soaking yourself?

06:44.721 --> 06:46.099
Is there any other way?

06:46.356 --> 06:48.523
Well, we're very much alike.

06:48.592 --> 06:49.891
[LAUGHS HAUGHTILY]

06:49.960 --> 06:51.860
It's almost as if we could
complete each other's...

06:51.928 --> 06:53.795
[TOGETHER] Thoughts from my
brain that turn into words

06:53.864 --> 06:55.778
and, added together, become...

06:56.232 --> 06:57.932
word piles.

06:58.001 --> 06:59.467
[SWELLING ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

06:59.536 --> 07:00.904
Who are you?

07:01.438 --> 07:03.071
Would you like to dance with me?

07:03.362 --> 07:05.962
Maybe somewhere... private?

07:06.509 --> 07:07.942
Normally, I wouldn't dance with a stranger,

07:08.011 --> 07:10.078
but this feels like...

07:10.496 --> 07:11.881
- Fate.
- Two gorillas.

07:15.178 --> 07:17.096
[GRUNTING]

07:22.292 --> 07:23.826
[GLASS SHATTERING]

07:28.598 --> 07:29.831
[GLASS CRUNCHING, FABRIC TEARING]

07:29.900 --> 07:33.201
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow, butt cut! Butt cut!

07:33.270 --> 07:35.203
I cut my butt! Ah! Ow!

07:35.272 --> 07:36.571
[FABRIC RIPPING]

07:36.640 --> 07:38.606
Ooh, ooh, my dress! [SQUEALS]

07:38.675 --> 07:40.775
Ow, ow...

07:40.844 --> 07:42.798
[GRUNTING]

07:43.680 --> 07:44.846
[GASPS]

07:45.254 --> 07:47.682
[GASPING]

07:47.918 --> 07:49.350
Oh, I'm bleeding.

07:49.419 --> 07:51.126
Ah, oh, butt cut.

07:51.588 --> 07:52.584
Help!

07:53.156 --> 07:54.148
Oh...

08:00.730 --> 08:02.297
- What's this?
- [GASPS]

08:02.365 --> 08:03.798
What are you doing in here?

08:03.867 --> 08:06.601
All the young ladies are
lining up for Colonel Trimbald.

08:06.670 --> 08:07.936
You can't miss it.

08:08.004 --> 08:09.771
Oh, I-I-I... No,
no, m-my dress...

08:09.839 --> 08:11.439
It's all right, virgin. Follow me.

08:11.508 --> 08:13.074
- Ooh, ah, ah...
- Right this way.

08:13.572 --> 08:15.238
[QUIETLY] Oh, Colonel Trimbald...

08:17.353 --> 08:19.754
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

08:19.822 --> 08:22.436
Mm, wonderful curtsy, yes!

08:22.436 --> 08:24.570
Oh, very nice form.

08:24.639 --> 08:27.373
Ahem. Located another rogue virgin, sir.

08:27.441 --> 08:29.208
Ooh, my!

08:29.277 --> 08:31.010
[TITTERS]

08:31.078 --> 08:32.678
Oh, ho, ho!

08:32.746 --> 08:34.513
Colonel Trimbald doesn't want a woman.

08:34.582 --> 08:36.102
He wants a child.

08:36.859 --> 08:38.558
I can play that game.

08:39.054 --> 08:42.048
Well, aren't you a vision?

08:43.698 --> 08:46.800
This isn't my first
"sexiest curtsy" contest.

08:46.869 --> 08:49.736
[LAUGHS] You have a
lot of spunk, don't you?

08:49.805 --> 08:51.672
I could always use more!

08:51.740 --> 08:52.973
Oh! [LAUGHS]

08:53.042 --> 08:55.342
Well, ladies, I want you all,

08:55.411 --> 08:57.644
but sadly, I can only choose one of you

08:57.713 --> 09:01.576
to dance with first, so who shall it be?

09:01.850 --> 09:02.916
ALL: Me, me, me!

09:02.985 --> 09:04.484
Oh, oh, oh!

09:04.553 --> 09:07.458
It's just overwhelming. I
don't know how to decide.

09:07.521 --> 09:08.953
You're all so perfect.

09:09.022 --> 09:10.321
So young,

09:10.390 --> 09:13.792
so unformed, so moldable.

09:13.860 --> 09:15.093
Pick me! I've been trained

09:15.162 --> 09:17.162
in both English and Continental fork use.

09:17.230 --> 09:19.664
I can learn to sing all
of your favorite cantatas,

09:19.733 --> 09:21.833
even the ones in the Catholic languages.

09:21.902 --> 09:24.069
[SCOFFS] I can speak
so softly and sweetly,

09:24.137 --> 09:26.237
you'll never even know I'm talking.

09:26.306 --> 09:28.306
My skin is so unblemished...

09:28.375 --> 09:30.241
[CHILDLIKE VOICE] I haven't got my period!

09:30.310 --> 09:31.311
What?

09:31.745 --> 09:33.645
I'm pwee-pubescent!

09:33.713 --> 09:36.781
Oh, ho, ho, ho! You are a delight!

09:36.850 --> 09:38.483
- [GIGGLES]
- Oh, yes!

09:38.552 --> 09:40.785
Half of my teeth are still baby teeth.

09:40.854 --> 09:44.289
Nice try, sweetie, but
I wasn't born yesterday.

09:44.357 --> 09:46.074
- Or was I? [GIGGLES]
- Oh!

09:46.660 --> 09:49.127
Oh, ho, ho, ho! A newborn!

09:49.196 --> 09:50.829
[DELIGHTED LAUGHTER]

09:50.897 --> 09:52.664
[LAUGHTER]

09:52.732 --> 09:54.056
What's going on in here?

09:55.328 --> 09:56.633
Clean the andirons!

09:56.718 --> 09:57.951
They are clean, sir.

09:58.020 --> 09:59.874
Flobelle made a schedule,
and we finished early.

09:59.928 --> 10:02.187
Well, uh, rotate the soup ware.

10:02.312 --> 10:04.312
They've been rotated and re-rotated.

10:04.380 --> 10:06.047
Flobelle had me do it hours ago.

10:06.115 --> 10:07.982
She's one step ahead of you, Garfield.

10:08.051 --> 10:11.401
Funny. She makes me want to do my job.

10:11.526 --> 10:14.121
Well, Miss Lillian and
Beatrice will be home soon.

10:14.190 --> 10:16.090
We must prepare the post-party chamber.

10:16.159 --> 10:18.025
It's already done. This one.

10:18.094 --> 10:19.994
[LAUGHTER]

10:20.063 --> 10:21.662
Flobelle, it's usually

10:21.731 --> 10:24.131
the head butler's job to give the orders.

10:24.200 --> 10:26.367
- Oh.
- Well, I just asked myself,

10:26.436 --> 10:27.902
"What would Garfield do?"

10:27.971 --> 10:29.203
And then I did it.

10:29.398 --> 10:30.972
Oh, well, can you ask,

10:31.040 --> 10:32.540
"Where would Garfield put the dustpans?"

10:32.608 --> 10:34.552
Because I cannot find them anywhere.

10:35.044 --> 10:38.646
[LIGHT WALTZ MUSIC]

10:38.715 --> 10:40.247
And then a priest, a rabbi and a Prussian

10:40.316 --> 10:41.415
walk into a bar.

10:41.484 --> 10:42.717
[LAUGHTER]

10:42.785 --> 10:45.252
That's the funniest thing I've ever heard.

10:45.321 --> 10:47.054
I have to be honest with you, lady.

10:47.459 --> 10:50.558
I just got out of a
35-year-long relationship.

10:50.626 --> 10:53.426
So did I. I was in one
that lasted my whole life.

10:55.004 --> 10:57.431
Wait. That ring... You're married?

10:57.500 --> 10:59.455
Oh, yes, but she's gross. I hate her.

10:59.544 --> 11:01.533
Can I tell you something
that I've never told anyone?

11:01.612 --> 11:03.311
- Yes.
- One time, my pony

11:03.380 --> 11:04.479
got an embarrassing haircut,

11:04.548 --> 11:06.370
and it was the worst day of my life!

11:07.224 --> 11:09.591
I am so touched that you told me that.

11:10.814 --> 11:13.087
This is the opposite of
the worst day of my life.

11:13.150 --> 11:14.838
- [SOFTLY EXCLAIMS]
- This is...

11:16.693 --> 11:18.293
A pretty good day.

11:21.526 --> 11:23.305
Well, I have a feeling it's about to get

11:23.330 --> 11:24.866
a whole lot better.

11:26.358 --> 11:28.919
[BOTH MOANING SOFTLY]

11:32.440 --> 11:35.542
I could listen to you talk
about toilets all night long!

11:35.610 --> 11:37.744
You know, we have a
saying in the toilet industry

11:37.812 --> 11:40.246
that a good toilet is a better listener

11:40.315 --> 11:41.460
than it is a talker.

11:41.460 --> 11:43.646
I don't understand what that means.

11:43.671 --> 11:46.388
It means it takes in
more than it spits out.

11:46.388 --> 11:48.556
Ooh! I never spit out.

11:48.595 --> 11:52.220
Oh, ho, you're a sweet
little toilet, aren't you?

11:52.318 --> 11:54.184
You know, a lot of girls say they're 11

11:54.253 --> 11:55.519
when they're really 15.

11:55.587 --> 11:57.921
I would never lie to you.

11:57.990 --> 12:01.058
If there's one thing I
can't abide by, it's liars

12:01.083 --> 12:03.423
and women born before 1890.

12:03.556 --> 12:05.156
Can I steal her for a moment?

12:05.224 --> 12:07.825
Ooh, Grandma! Only for a moment, though.

12:07.894 --> 12:10.795
As you know, it's almost past my bedtime.

12:10.863 --> 12:12.763
[GIGGLES]

12:12.832 --> 12:14.298
What the hell are you doing here?

12:14.367 --> 12:15.833
I am in the middle of some very sensitive

12:15.902 --> 12:17.001
political maneuvering.

12:17.070 --> 12:18.502
Well, maybe you should have

12:18.571 --> 12:19.937
thought of that before you
invited me to your party.

12:20.006 --> 12:21.605
I didn't invite you to my party!

12:21.674 --> 12:23.441
- Exactly!
- What is even your plan here?

12:23.509 --> 12:24.909
I don't know if you've noticed,

12:24.977 --> 12:27.078
but you aren't exactly the Colonel's type.

12:27.146 --> 12:28.379
[HIGH-PITCHED] Aren't I?

12:28.448 --> 12:30.614
The mask has to come
off eventually, Lillian.

12:30.683 --> 12:32.416
What is your long game?

12:32.485 --> 12:35.119
Joke's on you, Celery.
I don't have a long game.

12:35.188 --> 12:36.987
I never think more than one step ahead.

12:37.056 --> 12:39.924
They don't call me Lillian
"Small Picture" Bellacourt

12:39.992 --> 12:41.057
for nothing.

12:42.128 --> 12:43.060
[FALSETTO] Oops!

12:43.129 --> 12:44.929
[LAUGHTER]

